# Why Does This Work?

For every subarray

```
sum = prefix[right+1] - prefix[left]
```

If

```
sum > 0
```

then

```
2 × targetCount > length
```

which means

```
targetCount > length / 2
```

Hence the target is the majority element.

---

# Complexity Analysis

### Time Complexity

* Transform array → **O(n)**
* Prefix Sum → **O(n)**
* Coordinate Compression → **O(n log n)**
* Fenwick operations → **O(n log n)**

**Overall:**

```
O(n log n)
```

### Space Complexity

* Prefix array → **O(n)**
* Compressed values → **O(n)**
* Fenwick Tree → **O(n)**

**Overall:**

```
O(n)
```

## Summary

| Approach                  | Time           | Space    |
| ------------------------- | -------------- | -------- |
| Brute Force               | **O(n²)**      | **O(1)** |
| Prefix Sum + Fenwick Tree | **O(n log n)** | **O(n)** |

This optimal approach is suitable for the constraint **`n ≤ 10^5`** and passes all test cases.
